{
  "stem": "20711.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I am sure the stories they were telling, we couldn't even believe it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The only time we realize this people do telling the story, do telling the truth, when the Germans came home-- came into Hungary, this couple was found dead, hanging in a attic.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "By that time, they knew the same thing come to Hungary which came to Slovakia, and they were not about to live it through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And after that incident, everybody in town took it seriously.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And in a long run, I am so thankful for life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I did had a chance to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I knew they will be deported, even so it was no ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I knew it's a matter of days they will have to leave.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was able to meet everybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember one time my father's sister, who was an old maid, and she came over with a big, old-fashioned family album, one of those heavy duty, heavy pages.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she made my brother and I sit down, and she said, you must remember that in case you survive, you must remember your grandparents.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "This is how they looked like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "This is their wedding photo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This is the family, and this is so-and-so.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And everybody was in that book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Some of the member of the family, I never met.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "There was one brother of my father who emigrated to Israel in the '30s, and I don't remember them, but they were in that photo album.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we paged through patiently and slowly, and she attached a story to almost every picture.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And she brought over some relics in the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My grandmother had a beautiful Brussels lace shawl she wore in holidays, and it was always put back into the original box.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
